{"id":678,"date":"2023-11-03T18:55:37","date_gmt":"2023-11-03T11:55:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/?page_id=678"},"modified":"2023-11-04T13:58:56","modified_gmt":"2023-11-04T06:58:56","slug":"visiting-hunre-in-hanoi-vietnam","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/visiting-hunre-in-hanoi-vietnam\/","title":{"rendered":"Visiting HUNRE"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Welcome to HUNRE, Hanoi, and thank you for choosing GIS-IDEAS,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This year, GIS-IDEAS and Hanoi University of Natural Resources and Environment (HUNRE) cooperated in Ha Noi, Vietnam. We, HUNRE, are proud to present you with several places worth visiting when you stay in this fantastic city. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\">\n<p><strong>Firstly, the weather is humid and hot<\/strong>. <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>You can find the weather forecast <a href=\"https:\/\/www.timeanddate.com\/weather\/vietnam\/hanoi\/ext\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.timeanddate.com\/weather\/vietnam\/hanoi\/ext\"><strong>HERE<\/strong><\/a>. The photo below shows the weather forecast for the conference days. So, keep your head up for the newest update. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.timeanddate.com\/weather\/vietnam\/hanoi\/ext\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"447\" src=\"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/Weather_update-1024x447.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-686\" srcset=\"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/Weather_update-1024x447.png 1024w, https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/Weather_update-300x131.png 300w, https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/Weather_update-768x335.png 768w, https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/Weather_update.png 1331w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/a><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\">\n<p><strong>Secondly, what should you get ready before visiting us? <\/strong><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Note the hot and rainy weather, so please bring your umbrella. But if you are sun-favor, a hat is still a good option.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The currency is the Vietnamese Dong, please change some cash at the airport. It will be so much helpful.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can look for more information about visiting Hanoi, with many places to visit. For example, <a href=\"https:\/\/vietnam.travel\/things-to-do\/explore-old-quarter-your-way\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https:\/\/vietnam.travel\/things-to-do\/explore-old-quarter-your-way\"><strong>the old square<\/strong><\/a>. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, HUNRE is not too far away from the center but still easy to find. All <a href=\"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/travel\/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/travel\/\"><strong>suggested hotels<\/strong><\/a> are quite close to HUNRE so you can easily take a taxi and public transportation to get to us. You can find the bus that regularly passes HUNRE <a href=\"http:\/\/timbus.vn\/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"http:\/\/timbus.vn\/\"><strong>here<\/strong><\/a>. In particular, bus number 05 stops every 15 to 20 minutes with a ticket price of 7,000 VND. And remember you have other options, like a Grab bike or Grab car, at a more reasonable price than a taxi.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/maps\/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3723.674225961752!2d105.76170937008358!3d21.04571717582321!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x313454c3ce577141%3A0xb1a1ac92701777bc!2sHanoi%20University%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20and%20Environment!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1699011701650!5m2!1sen!2s\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"><\/iframe>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Welcome to HUNRE, Hanoi, and thank you for choosing GIS-IDEAS, This year, GIS-IDEAS and Hanoi University of Natural Resources and&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/678"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=678"}],"version-history":[{"count":11,"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/678\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":702,"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/678\/revisions\/702"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/gis-ideas.org\/2023\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=678"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}